<% current_help_step = HelpStep.find(6) %>
<%= render :partial => "content", locals: { current_help_step: current_help_step } %>
<h1 class="part-title">Start making allocations</h1>
<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  This step must be completed by a head of offender management delivery (HOMD) or head of offender management services
  (HOMS).
</div>

<div class="govuk-grid-column">
  <div class="govuk-body">
    <p>Once all the steps in this guide have been completed, you are ready to make allocations. </p>

    <p>
      You can do this in the

      <%=
        link_to(
          'Make new allocations',
          'prisons/LEI/prisoners/unallocated'
        )
      %>

      part of the service.
    </p>

    <p>
      If this is the first time you are allocating cases to your team using this service, your allocations will need to
      mirror existing ones. For example, if an POM is working with a prisoner, then you will need to assign
      that same POM to the prisoner.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
